nodes.title: Scheduler & Sampler
widgets_values:
My default settings:
---
1st KSampler:

>Sampler:    uni_pc
\
Scheduler:  simple

2nd KSampler:

>Sampler:    lcm
\
Scheduler:  simple

---

You can try others if you want to experiment.

Leave the rest of the settings as it is.

nodes.title: Start Steps End Steps Input Info for KSampler
widgets_values:
1st KSampler:

>Start step has to be from 0.
\
End Step is where you want the process to end.

2nd KSampler:

>Start Step is where left off from the 1st KSampler.
\
End Step just leave it at 10000. It will end at total Steps.

---
Example:

1st KSampler: Start 0 - End 5   
\
2nd KSampler: Start 5 - End 10000

With a Total Steps of 8.

It will go through 5 Step in the 1st KSampler

And finish it with 3 Steps in the second.

nodes.title: Settings
widgets_values:
## Steps input:

>Start Steps: 5 \
End Steps: 3
 
are recommended from personal testing.

You can try:

>Start Steps: 4 \
End Steps: 3 

---
## Speed input:

>1 = normal speed

>more than 1 = accelerated motion but reduce video length

>Less than 1 = slow down motion but increase video length

-----
Try not go below 0.6 speed.

nodes.title: Known Errors:
widgets_values:
When you encountered this error:

> KSamplerAdvanced Expected all tensors to be on the same device, but found at least two devices, cpu and cuda:0! (when checking argument for argument mat1 in method wrapper_CUDA_addmm)

Disable/Delete BlockSwap and VRAM-Cleanup nodes.

Ensure you have enough VRAM.

@damiang

nodes.title: Interpolation For External Workflow
widgets_values:
🚨🚨🚨🢂
🢂
🢂


## Do not enable and use it here.

This is a Frame Interpolation  template for external workflow with Interpolation Multiplier and Speed Input.

Copy the whole box and paste it in an empty workflow. (Remember to enable it)

---
You can use any videos generated from any WF.

## But,

 it has to be videos that are NOT interpolated.

Can also add it into your WF.

---

You can safely delete this box. 🢂

nodes.title: Merger For External Workflow
widgets_values:
🚨🚨🚨🢂
🢂
🢂


## Do not enable and use it here.

This is a video Merger/Joiner template for external workflow with Interpolation Multiplier and Speed Input.

## It does not Interpolate Frames !

Copy the whole box and paste it in an empty workflow. (Remember to enable it)

---
You can use any videos generated from any WF.

## But,

Make sure both videos have the same interpolation multipliers.

You can still merge 2 vids with different multipliers but they will run at different speed.

Examples.
>1st vid interpolated at 4x
\
2nd vid interpolated at 2x

If you merge them at x4. 1st vid will appears normal while the 2nd vid will look 2x faster.

If you merge them at x2. 1st vid will appears slower while the 2nd vid will look normal.



---

You can add frame interpolation with this if you want and know how to.

---

You can safely delete this box. 🢂

nodes.title: Get & Set Node Searching
widgets_values:
## Nodes Map Search (Shift+m)

🚨🚨🚨🚨
Only available if you have "ComfyUI-Easy-Use" custom nodes installed. 
🚨🚨🚨🚨

In your Comfyui Interface panel. Usually on the left. Look for an icon with 1 small square on top and 3 small squares below it. It's call Nodes Map. 

---

Let say you see a "Set_FrameNum" node.

And you want to know where the "Get_FrameNum" is.

Enter in the search bar (Search by Node ID/Name...).
> Get_FramN....


--! Case Sensitive !--

And you will see it filtered.

Double click on that and it will bring you to the node.

---
Likewise for Get nodes.

"Set_FrameNum"

Search: 
>Get_FrameNum

Double click.

widgets_values:
Default Start CFG 5. (3 - 6)
\
Do not change End CFG (1).

3 seems good for some loras.

Alt between 5 and 3 and see which is better.

nodes.title: Model Route
widgets_values:
🡹 Start of 3rd Model Route: 

Split into 2 routes.

---

>One for 1st sampler with CausVid (Strength: 0.3).

>The other for 2nd sampler with Self-Force Lora. (Strength: 1)

nodes.title: CausVid Lora Strength Info
widgets_values:
## CausVid Lora Strength

0.3 Defualt.

>Range: 0.3 - 1

-----------------------------------
More strength might give more motion.

However, some lora can be overcooked when using higher strength.

If you experience grey out first few frames when using higher strength, reduce CausVid Lora Strength or set it to 0.3.

-----
## For Experimental Purpose

CausVid can indeed increase motion, but can seems very unnatural. 

If you want to experiment to have more natural motion. 

You can combine Self-forcing and CausVid in the 1st model route while  Self-forcing at strength 1 in the 2nd model route.

But balancing the strength of both will be a tricky one.

Example:
>Self-forcing: 0.7
\
CausVid: 0.4

When using this setup, I did experience some weird "Hallucinating"/unwanted object appearing or a person walking out of nowhere.

Self-forcing makes motion more natural. But using it alone have less motion compare to CausVid.
